OL,5, X, formerly called Twitter, has removed
OL,6, a post denying the Holocaust after     
OL,7, criticism from the Auschwitz Museum.   
OL,8, The social media platform had initially
OL,9, said the post did not break its rules. 
OL,11,FThe offensive post was a reply to one  
OL,12,Ffrom the museum about a three year-old 
OL,13,FJewish girl murdered in the            
OL,14,Fconcentration camp's gas chambers.     
OL,16,FThe post called her death a "fairy     
OL,17,Ftale" and used anti-Semitic tropes.    
OL,19,FX's policies state that Holocaust      
OL,20,Fdenial is prohibited.                  
